{"word":"G2878 - κορβᾶν - korbân - kor-ban' - Corban","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">κορβᾶν</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>korbân"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>kor-ban'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Corban"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"காணிக்கை, கொர்பான் - ஆண்பால் பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"1. korban, a gift"},{"paragraph":"2. the sacred treasury"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Masculine / பெயர்ச்சொல் (ஆண்பால்)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Of Hebrew and Chaldee origin respectively [<a href=\"#/H7133 - קׇרְבָּן - qorbân - kor-bawn'/7133\">H7133</a>]; a votive <i>offering</i> and <i>the offering</i>; a <i>consecrated present</i> (to the Temple fund); by extension (the latter term) the <i>Treasury</i> itself, that is, the room where the contribution boxes stood: - Corban, treasury."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"}]}